text.0: Planning for #Thanksgiving? Consider hosting a virtual meal with friends and family who don’t live with you. Have people share recipes and show off their turkey, dressing, and other dishes: https://t.co/tdoJgRfnQl https://t.co/haOj1Rw2vs
text.1: Let’s talk turkey! This #Thanksgiving, use a food thermometer to check the internal temperature of your turkey and stuffing. 165° F is best. LEARN MORE about safe food handling this holiday season: https://t.co/WUWuOSd1PV #FoodSafety https://t.co/kbAKByNVpH

text.3: It’s “Public Health Thank You Day” today, and I’d like to recognize all our public health heroes for their resiliency in the face of this ongoing pandemic. Thank you for all that you continue you to do, and especially for staying #FDAStrong! #PHTYD https://t.co/fYdwkIUW7z
